FOR REGISTERED NEW JERSEY BREDS FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON ONE NEW JERSEY BRED RESTRICTED RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 12 1 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 22 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (Rail at 17 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEA MAIDEN vied three wide for the lead, dueled on the turn and into the stretch, took over past the furlong marker and drew clear under urging. PERSPICACIOUS was bumped and off a bit slow, raced off the pace inside, chased the leaders on the turn, rallied steadily outside in the stretch run and was up late for second. AMAZING GRACES JOY vied between rivals for the lead, dueled on the turn and into the stretch, came over bumping DELIGHTFUL AVA at the furlong marker, then dug in to the finish. DELIGHTFUL AVA vied inside for the lead, dueled on the turn, dueled on the rail in upper stretch, then was bumped and forced to check at the eighth pole and weakened after. RACHEL CAROLINE was off a bit slow, raced off the pace inside and closed belatedly. TOOT YOUR HORN was bumped, off slowly and steadied, then chased two wide and lacked a rally. After a Stewards' Inquiry and Jockey Objection, AMAZING GRACES JOY was disqualified and placed fourth for interference at the eighth pole.
